<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">856e.00/9–748: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss> at
                                    Batavia</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-09T18:00:00-04:00">September 9, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>411. Dept appreciates info Congentel 763 Sep 7 and is deeply
                                concerned Communist threat to present moderate Repub regime.
                                Accordingly if you think desirable, you may your discretion
                                communicate to Hatta following: <list>
                                    <label>
                                        <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>US Govt will in every practical way assist democratic
                                        non-Communist govt of Indonesia successfully to resist
                                        Communist tyranny.</item>
                                    <label>
                                        <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Dept believes stability Hatta regime best assured through
                                        acceptance both parties just and practical settlement
                                        Dutch-Repub dispute. US now making every effort find basis
                                        such settlement. For ConGen info, Dept will back Cochran
                                        plan (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 366<note n="1" xml:id="d243fn1">Telegrams 750–60, September 6, none
                                            printed, but see footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_322">p.
                                                322</ref>.</note> and 367<note n="2" xml:id="d243fn2">Telegram 761, September 7, <ref target="#pg_322">p. 322</ref>.</note> and <gloss target="#t_Usgoc1">Usgoc</gloss> 135<note n="3" xml:id="d243fn3">
                                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> and will request
                                        Neth Emb to secure Hague support. Coordinate, therefore,
                                        your representations this point with Cochran.</item>
                                    <label>
                                        <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Dept will support extension financial help in which all
                                        states of peaceful federation Indonesia would share
                                        according to their needs and dependent upon their capacity
                                        utilize shares of loans efficiently and as sound borrowers.
                                        For ConGen info, Cochran requested permission (<gloss target="#t_Gocus1">Gocus</gloss> 367) to use this
                                        language in representations to Repub. Therefore, you should
                                        coordinate carefully with Cochran on this point <pb facs="0342" n="328" xml:id="pg_328"/> determining with
                                        him which of you can most effectively make use of this
                                            approach.<note n="4" xml:id="d243fn4">Repeated as 431 to
                                            The Hague.</note>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>